  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hey Rohan, I heard you used the phrase 'His playing is so graceful' — that was a lovely choice! Tell me, did you watch any football lately?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah! I watch football almost every day. Yesterday I saw a match between Real Madrid and Barcelona. The way Messi played was amar hawaya — literally took my breath away. Also, I try to learn new English words while watching commentaries. It helps a lot, I think."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That is a great idea! I like how you said \"amar hawaya\" — you could say, \"it took my breath away\" in English. You're doing well! Tell me, did you learn any new words yesterday?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I did! The commentator said \"dominant\" and \"fluid passing\". I looked them up later. Dominant means a team is controlling the game, right? And fluid passing is when the ball moves smoothly between players. I also heard the word \"tactical\" — but I’m not sure about that one. Maybe it means a team is playing with a plan?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great! \"Dominant\" is correct — a team is dominant when it controls the game. \"Fluid passing\" is perfect too! For \"tactical,\" you're right: it means a team plays with a plan. Well done! What’s your favorite word you’ve learned so far?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My favorite word is \"graceful\" — I used it to describe a player's movement last week. It makes me feel proud when I can use a big word correctly. Oh, and I also like \"resilient.\" I learned it from a movie, actually — it means being strong even after facing problems, right?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I love how you use \"graceful\" — it’s a beautiful word! And \"resilient\" is a great one too. You're right, it means being strong after facing problems. You're learning so well! What movie did you hear it in?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It was in a movie called \"Bhonsle\" — it’s a Bengali film, by the way. The main character is very resilient after many struggles. I like that word because it sounds strong and meaningful. By the way, do you watch football? I’d love to know your favorite player!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Rohan, \"Bhonsle\" sounds interesting — I will look for it! I do watch football and my favorite player is Messi too. His playing is so graceful! What about you — any other favorite players?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My favorite player is also Messi! I also like Neymar because he plays with so much creativity. Sometimes I follow the Indian Super League too, though it's not as good as the European leagues. Do you like football or are you more into other sports?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I like football too — and I enjoy how creative Neymar is! The Indian Super League is fun to watch as well. I also like cricket, but football is my first love. What made you start watching football?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I started watching football because my dad is a huge fan. He used to play a lot when he was young, and he introduced me to the game. I got hooked after watching a World Cup match when I was 10 — the energy, the skill... it all felt amazing. Now I can’t imagine a day without football! Do you have a favorite team?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That’s such a nice story! I’m glad your dad shared his love for football with you. It sounds exciting! My favorite team is Barcelona — I love their style of play. What about you — any team you root for?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My favorite team is also Barcelona! I love how they play with so much control and teamwork. I also support Real Madrid because of Messi, but Barcelona is my heart’s team. Oh, and I follow AC Milan too — they’re doing well this season. What made you love Barcelona’s style?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I love Barcelona’s style because they play with patience and lots of passing — it feels like art! I admire how they work as a team. You’re right, they are amazing! What’s your favorite way to watch football — live, on TV, or online?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I mostly watch on TV or my phone — live matches are best, but they’re not always easy to watch here. Sometimes I rewatch highlights or clips to see how players move. It helps me learn English too — like when they describe a goal or a save. I also take notes! By the way, can I say \"I’m hooked on football\" or is there a better way?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You can definitely say \"I’m hooked on football\" — it’s natural and correct! Good choice! I like how you take notes — that’s a smart way to learn. What’s one thing you wrote down recently?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Recently, I wrote down \"he executed a perfect through ball\" — I didn’t know the word \"execute\" could mean doing something so exactly and well. I also wrote down \"the defense was shaky\" — I think it means they were not confident. I look at these notes when I feel stuck. Btw, do you think I can use \"shaky\" in other ways, like \"my voice was shaky\"?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, you can say \"my voice was shaky\" — it means you sounded nervous or uncertain. Very good use! \"Shaky\" works for many things, like hands, steps, or even confidence. What’s a time your voice felt shaky?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Once during a presentation at my bank interview prep class, I got so nervous my voice was completely shaky. I couldn't speak properly for a moment — it was embarrassing! Now I practice speaking in front of the mirror to get better. Football commentaries also help me get used to speaking in English. Do you get nervous before teaching sessions?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, sometimes I get nervous before sessions — but I remind myself that it's okay to feel that way! You're doing well by practicing in front of the mirror. What's one thing you're working on improving for your interview?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I’m working on my confidence and clarity when speaking in English — especially during group discussions. Also, I want to improve my knowledge of banking terms. I read a little every day and try to speak more. Today, I practiced explaining what a \"balance sheet\" is — it felt good! But I still get nervous. How do you stay calm during teaching?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great by practicing daily — that’s the key! I stay calm by taking deep breaths and reminding myself to enjoy the conversation. It helps a lot! What’s one banking term you learned recently?"
    }
  ],
